notesStmt.note: Title from caption title page (f. 2r); the name Copanabastla also appears in other sources as Copanahuaxtla and Copanaguastla. A note on previous page states, "De licentia sui prelati ad usum habet Fray Alonso de Guzman, Traslado este bocabulario el sobre dicho P[adr]e el año de 1620 años en la provinçia de los tzeldales en el pueblo de Taquinvitz" (f. 1r).
A manuscript of Domingo de Ara's Vocabulario de la lengua española y tzeldal, the model for Guzman's work, is also in this collection (Ms. Coll. 700, Item 185).

msContents.summary: Early 17th-century revision of Domingo de Ara's 16th-century Spanish-Tzeltal dictionary.

msItem.title: Vocabulario en lengua tzeldal iuxta ussum oppidii de Copanabastla

supportDesc.extent: 221 leaves : 208 x 142 mm. bound to 220 x 164 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 221; [2-5], 6-109, 109-181, 183-222; contemporary pagination in ink, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 29-32 long lines; alphabet letters as running title.

origin.p: Written in the Mexican state of Chiapas in 1620.

history.provenance: A note pasted to the flyleaves of Item 185 suggests that this volume, together with Item 185, passed through the collections of the abbé Brasseur de Bourbourg, A. L. Pinart, and Eugène Boban before Daniel Garrison Brinton purchased it separately from the Berendt collection. Unlike Item 185, this volume does not have a bookplate from the library of Brasseur de Bourbourg.
From the collection of Daniel Garrison Brinton (ex libris stamp on title page).
